HEADWORD: Incapsulation
<hw>In*cap`su*la"tion</hw> <pr>(?)</pr>, <pos>n.</pos>
<fld>(Physiol.)</fld> <def>The process of becoming, or the state or
condition of being, incapsulated; <as>as, <ex>incapsulation</ex> of the
ovum in the uterus</as>.</def>⟦br⟧
[<source>1913 Webster</source>]</p>

